
TPU Tuner mod

This is a non-official modification, by Joe Forster/STA, of the original TPU Tuner, by Stefan Reuther.
Original homepage: http://www.phost.de/~stefan/turbo.html

History

2025-09-19 (Joe Forster/STA)
- Bugfixes:
  - Hash tables in unit files are 2 bytes longer than indicated by the size descriptor. (This resulted in some function names - those in the last entry of hash tables - not getting listed with the "-n" switch.)
  - The two instructions "MOV reg, op2; POP reg" with the same register operand are not swapped; instead, the "MOV" is deleted as its effect is discarded anyway.
  - After a "MOV SP, whatever", the stack's state becomes unknown, therefore previously pushed values can't reliably be popped back; e.g. "PUSH op1; MOV SP, BP; POP reg" doesn't become "MOV SP, BP; MOV reg, op1".
  - Fixed misunderstood opcodes:
    - 27: "DAA" (not "ADD");
    - 2F: "DAS" (not "SUB");
    - 37: "AAA" (not "XOR");
    - 3F: "AAS" (not "CMP").
- Options:
  - Options can be read from files.
  - Added "-f" option to enable or disable (default) the removal of unused stack frames. (The corresponding code was mostly finished in the original program anyway.)
  - Added "-2" option to enable (default) or disable 286 instructions.
  - Added "--exclude" option to exclude functions from optimization (data in code segment, code for a non-x86 CPU etc.).
  - Added "--format-debug" option for some additional formatting in debug dumps.
  - Added more possibilites to turn off options.
- Debug files:
  - (Hexadecimal) numbers in debug file names are padded to 3 digits - "block000", "block008", "block010" etc. rather than "block0", "block8", "block10" etc. - so that they are better sorted in a directory list.
  - Function names, if available, are added to the beginning of debug files.
- Messages:
  - The "XXX bytes saved (new size = XXX)" message, for each function, is displayed only when code size actually changed.
  - An additional "XXX bytes added" message, for each function, and a "Code added: XXX" message, at the end of the unit, is displayed if the code became larger because of 286 instructions having been disabled.
