- Compilation:
  - Merged DJGPP- and MinGW-specific parts back into the main make file.
  - The Windows executable is linked statically (requires only msvcrt.dll).
- Source:
  - Converted Tabs to spaces.
  - Marked commented out code fragments with either "[DEBUG]" (debug-related) or "[OBSOLETE]" (not debug-related), to make them stand out from descriptive comments.
  - Turned instruction mnemonics and register names in comments to uppercase, for easier distinction of fixed (uppercase) and variable (lowercase) parts.
  - Standardized operand names in comments to "rX" (register, X bits), "rmX" (register or memory, X bits), "Sr" (segment register) and "ib"/"iw" (immediate, 8/16 bits).
  - The "I_MAX" value contains the number of instruction mnemonics. Instruction-related arrays are defined with it so that the compiler will complain if the number of initialization elements mismatches.
  - The -1 value stands for no value in the "param" field of "CInstruction" objects.

2013-10-01 (Joe Forster/STA)
- Bugfixes:
  - Removed changing "MOV Sr1, op1", when the first instruction of a function, to "PUSH Sr2; POP Sr1" (crash: null-pointer dereference).
  - Added check to skip changing the instruction "OR reg, reg" to itself (infinite loop of optimization passes).
- Fixed gcc errors:
  - Added inclusion of "cstdlib" (error: non-existing symbols).
  - Added some "using std::symbol" clauses (error: non-existing symbols).
  - Changed some "op1 != op2" expressions, with class-typed operands, to "!(op1 == op2)" (error: non-existing "!=" operator).
- Fixed gcc warnings:
  - Fixed skipping "op reg1, reg2, 0", when changing "MOV [mem], const [...]; MOV [mem], reg" to "MOV reg, const; JMP label; [...] label: MOV [mem],reg", probably resulting in a program crash as it accessed the 4th operand when there are only 3 (warning: array access beyond bounds).
  - Added parentheses around a non-trivial block of && and || operators. (warning: suggested parentheses)
  - Added DJGPP- and MinGW-specific make files.
- Added 32-bit Windows binary (requires libgcc_s_dw2-1.dll, libstdc++-6.dll and msvcrt.dll).
